  "key": "carsonella",
  "name": "Candidatus Carsonella ruddii Pv",
  "niche": {
    "entity_count": 60,
    "description": "Curated obligate-symbiont roster \u00d7 CDS GCF_000010365.1 ASM1036v1 (NCBI, public domain). 16 loci: the retained translation/replication core (EF-Tu/EF-G, DNA pol III, DnaK/GroEL, RNA polymerase, ribosomal proteins) + the amino-acid-biosynthesis PROVISIONING pathway (the leucine leuB/leuD + aromatic shikimate->chorismate aroC/aroK/aroB + threonine/aspartate genes) that Carsonella trades its sap-feeding psyllid host for shelter. ~159,662 bp / ~182 ORFs / ~16.5% GC / ~97.3% coding [Nakabachi 2006, Science 1134196] \u2014 one of the smallest cellular genomes; has SHED cell-envelope/nucleotide/lipid/DNA-repair machinery -> NO free-living phase (cannot free-live; the ObligateSymbiont role). The host-coupling kernel reads role + the SymbiosisCapacity lever, not specific genes (ADR-019 S5, Mode B obligate symbiont).",
    "temp_optimum": 0.6,
    "parent_key": null,
    "trophic_role": "symbiont",
    "host_key": "default"
  },
